&quot;pragnesh.p&quot; wrote:

&gt; Hi,
&gt;
&gt;         I have been asked to do some exploration on JUnit. I have finished exploration of JUnit and JUnitPerf and am currently exploring XmlUnit.
&gt;         There is a funny problem which i am facing currently. When I compile test_XMLTestCase.java (a sample file given) with
&gt;
&gt;     public static void main(String[] args) {
&gt;         (new junit.textui.TestRunner()).run(suite());
&gt;     }
&gt;
&gt; it compiles and runs without any problems.
&gt; However when i do the following change
&gt;
&gt;     public static void main(String[] args) {
&gt;         (new junit.swingui.TestRunner()).run(suite());
&gt;     }
&gt;
&gt; It gives following error:
&gt;
&gt; test_XMLTestCase.java:297: cannot resolve symbol
&gt; symbol  : method run  (junit.framework.TestSuite)
&gt; location: class junit.swingui.TestRunner
&gt;         (new junit.swingui.TestRunner()).run(suite());
&gt;         ^
&gt; 1 error
&gt;
&gt; Does any one have an idea of watz happening.
&gt;

The Swing UI&#39;s TestRunner uses run(Class test), rather than run(Test test).

Try:

    new junit.swingui.TestRunner().run(test_XMLTestCase.class);


